headline: Bath & Body Works Stock Tanked After Earnings. Directors Bought Up Shares.
summary: Bath & Body Works  stock tanked following the release of third-quarter numbers, compounding an already grim year for the retailer.  Six company directors recently bought up shares.  Shares plunged 25% on Nov. 20 to $15.82, their largest single-day percentage drop in over five years, after the retailer missed earnings projections and cut its fiscal-year forecast.
